olive oil
1 packet jasmine rice
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet button mushrooms
½ lemon
½ sachet black peppercorns
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend
2.5 tbs plain flour
¼ tsp salt
1 packet soy sauce mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 bag coriander

• Boil the kettle.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Add jasmine rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12-14 minutes.
• Drain, rinse with warm water and set aside. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Drain the sweetcorn. Thinly slice button mushrooms. Cut lemon into wedges. Crush black peppercorns (see ingredients) with a mortar and pestle or in their sachet using a rolling pin. Cut boneless chicken drumsticks into 2cm chunks.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot, sweetcorn and mushrooms until lightly browned, 4-6 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a large bowl and cover to keep warm.

• SPICY! Peppercorns can be spicy, use less if you're sensitive to heat! In a medium bowl, combine crushed peppercorns, Southeast Asian spice blend, the plain flour and the salt. Add chicken and toss to coat.
• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base. When oil is hot, pick up chicken using tongs and shake
off any excess flour back into the bowl.
• Cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.

TIP: Add a drizzle more oil if necessary!

• To the bowl of veggies, add cooked rice, soy sauce mix and a squeeze of lemon juice. Stir to combine.
• Divide Asian mushroom rice between bowls. Top with salt-pepper chicken and garlic aioli.
• Tear over coriander and serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch and tear over the coriander.